[32mBelow is an example of a composer.json file that specifies a PHP version requirement of either 7.1+ or 8+:

{
  "name": "vendor/package",
  "description": "A sample package that supports PHP 7.1+ or PHP 8+",
  "require": {
    "php": "^7.1 || ^8.0"
  }
}

Explanation:
• "^7.1 || ^8.0" means the package accepts any PHP version in the 7.1 series (7.1.x and above, up until 8.0) or any version in the 8.x series.
• Adjust "vendor/package" and "description" as necessary for your project.

Hope that helps![0m
